Anthrax Found at ABC
-----------------------------
ABCNEWS announced Tuesday that tests confirmed the presence of anthrax in a
small mailroom at the network's headquarters in New York. The 7-month-old
son of an ABCNEWS producer who visited the building tested positive for
cutaneous anthrax earlier this month, but the cause of the infant's
infection was not immediately known. The baby is recovering.
ABCNEWS President David Westin said the entire second floor, where the
contaminated mailroom is located, has been disinfected.
