Anthrax - Weapon Of Mass Destruction -- Over 60 Scientific Government
Reports Available From The National Technical Information Service
-----------------------------------------
SPRINGFIELD, Va.: Throughout the 1990s, the federal government recognized
the dangers of biological weapons as weapons of mass destruction (WMD). In
1995, the United States made one of its highest priorities developing
effective capabilities to detect, prevent, defeat, and manage the
consequences of nuclear, biological and chemical (NBC) materials or weapons
use by terrorists.
In response to requests from researchers, subject specialists at NTIS have
searched its database of nearly 3 million U.S. government scientific,
technical, and business related information products. A bibliography of the
reports they found on anthrax can be accessed on the NTIS website at :
<http://www.ntis.gov/product/featured/anthrax.htm>
